name: Meteor shower tonight
summary: Tonight marks the peak of the Geminid meteor shower, one of the most impressive astronomical events of the year. Originating from the constellation Gemini, the meteor shower is known for its high visibility and potential to produce up to 120 meteors per hour. If conditions are favorable, observers in various locations, including Philadelphia, New York, Chicago, and Florida, will have the opportunity to witness this celestial display. To optimize visibility, find a dark, open area away from artificial lights and allow your eyes to adjust to the darkness for at least 20 minutes. The Geminids' meteor shower serves as a fitting end to the year's celestial calendar and promises a spectacular night sky experience.

name: Nestor Cortes
summary: In a significant trade, the New York Yankees have acquired All-Star closer Devin Williams from the Milwaukee Brewers in exchange for starting pitcher Nestor Cortes Jr. and pitching prospect Caleb Durbin.
